                    </div>
                    <span>This is a great book! A read it about a year ago and plan to re-read it all over again. Excellent historical perspective...unfortunately, humans rarely have learnt from past experience...I value this book from the point that it neither tells you what the future will be, nor giving advice on what to do. One should never assume that someone else would give all advices on what/how/where...Be your own shepherd, but learn from past generations...And this is when this book may help you...
<br />One a negative side, I would agree that some material expressed in the book, appears to be a compilation of the Daily Reckonning letters (of which I am a long term subscriber), but hey, would you rather have it in one book in ordered logical style, or scattered across hundreds of electronic letters?...
<br />Get the book, read it, learn from it - it will help you in doing your own diligence.</span>
                  
